<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="eab46b55-6711-5493-9452-56cdb386d563" activityNameId="7698be7d-fe98-4e6e-8a76-abfa114ff100" parentActivityId="eda21332-e0fc-58d6-88ab-5134908e3e3d" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of waste yarn and waste textile, unsanitary landfill</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to the environment (air via landfill gas, water via landfill leachate, and subsequent into groundwater). </includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'waste yarn and waste textile' in an unsanitary landfill. Recommended use of this dataset: for waste material going to unsanitary landfill, as part of unsorted, unmanaged, unscavenged municipal waste mixture. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% waste yarn and waste textile. Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 16.92 MJ/kg; net heating value 15.72 MJ/kg; H2O 20000; O 461180; H 58257; C 417780; S na; N na; P na; B na; Cl na; Br na; F na; I na; Ag na; As na; Ba na; Cd 0.0046491; Co na; Cr na; Cu 149.09; Hg na; Mn 22.89; Mo na; Ni na; Pb na; Sb na; Se na; Sn na; V na; Zn 25.887; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si na; Fe 133.72; Ca 0.13758; Al na; K na; Mg na; Na na. Share of carbon in initial waste waste that is biogenic 100%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts); Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 12%. 0 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period. </text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="9a63625a-358b-4c1d-bf95-50ba038a759b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents a landfill site with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 16.743579766537 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 1250.84108527132 mm/year, and net infiltration of 790.252035689178 mm/year. The leachate percolating through the landfill has an average residence time of 4.75 years. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference for climatic parameters: calculated average of national meteorological agencies for 83 countries based on undata, 2020. Precipitation, Environment Statistics Database, United Nations Statistics Division Available at: http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=precipitation&amp;d=ENV&amp;f=variableID%3a6</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is an inventory for an unsanitary, sub-controlled landfill for municipal solid waste. Ultimate average landfill height is 15 meters. Operation phase duration is 25 years. The total raw landfill gas mass produced in the landfill from this waste is 0.114 kg. The total CH4 mass in the raw landfill gas is 0.05083 kg. Percentage of landfill gas directly emitted is 100w%. Leachate of the landfill is not treated, but emitted untreated. Based on average waste composition and climate data the end of carbonate phase is estimated to be reached 2172 years after waste deposition. </text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2010-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
